<item>
            <title>[LU-18958] TCU: add NOTRASH attribute for files and directories</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18958</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It should be possible to add a &lt;tt&gt;NOTRASH&lt;/tt&gt; attribute to a file or directory, so that when it is deleted the MDS will bypass the Trash Can completely and delete the file immediately (as it was without the Trash Can feature).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the &lt;tt&gt;NOTRASH&lt;/tt&gt; attribute is set on a directory, then new files in that directory will inherit the &lt;tt&gt;NOTRASH&lt;/tt&gt; attribute.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is intended to mark directories that contain very temporary files that should not consume space in the Trash Can.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
